		<h3>Introduction</h3>
		<p>
			Welcome to RackMonkey help. RackMonkey's documentation is still a work in progress, check the <a href="http://www.rackmonkey.org/docs/1.2.4">online docs</a> for updates.
			You may find it helpful to open the help section in a separate tab or window so you can read it while working on RackMonkey.
			In the RackMonkey help parts of the interface are referred to like this: [Config > Organisations], this means select the Config tab at the top of the screen then choose organisations.
		</p>
		<p><strong>Tip:</strong> Hovering your mouse over many items (such as buttons) provides additional information.</p>
		
		<h3>RackMonkey Organisation</h3>
		<ul>
			<li>Servers, routers, switches etc. are <strong>devices</strong> and are contained within <strong>racks</strong>.</li>
			<li>A <strong>device</strong> has a <strong>hardware</strong> model and an <strong>operating system</strong>.</li>
			<li>A <strong>device</strong> has a <strong>domain</strong>, a <strong>role</strong>, a <strong>customer</strong> and a <strong>service level</strong>.</li>
			<li><strong>Racks</strong> are organised in <strong>rows</strong> which reside in <strong>rooms</strong> within <strong>buildings</strong>.</li>
		</ul>
		
		<h3>Getting Started</h3>
		<p>
			If you have just installed RackMonkey you should read the <a href="<TMPL_VAR NAME=base_url>?view=help&amp;view_type=getting_started">Getting Started Guide</a>. Otherwise, read on to get an introduction to using RackMonkey.
		</p>
				
		<h3>Finding and Viewing a Device</h3>
		<p>
			If you select [Devices] from the top nav bar you will get a complete list of all the devices you have recorded in RackMonkey. You can sort any of the columns by clicking on its name and use the filter dropdowns to restrict which devices are displayed.
		</p>
		<p>You can customise the device list view by selecting alternative views from the 'View Type' dropdown at the top left of the view. This allows you to see device asset information, extended information or just those devices currently not racked.</p>
		<p>
			To see a device in its rack, simple click on its location in the rack column. This will take you to the relevant rack view with the device highlighted.
		</p>
